---
import SiteLayout from '@/layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---
<SiteLayout title="Work" description="Ways to work with Sasha Vinčić on AI engineering, workshops, and technical leadership.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="mb-5 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-base-500">Work</p>
    <h1 class="max-w-4xl font-serif text-6xl font-light leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-7xl">I help teams make AI useful in real engineering work.</h1>
    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6"><h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">AI engineering workshops</h2><p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">Practical sessions for teams that need to understand agents, coding workflows, evaluation, and what should actually change in their day-to-day work.</p></article>
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6"><h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">Technical leadership</h2><p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">Architecture, codebase health, engineering process, mentoring, and product-aware technical judgement.</p></article>
      <article class="border-t border-base-300 pt-6"><h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-light">Prototypes that teach</h2><p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-base-600">Small, working systems that reveal what is hard, what is possible, and what should not be built.</p></article>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-12"><a href="/contact/" class="rounded-full bg-base-950 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-base-800">Get in touch</a></p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
